pling with climate warming and other emergencies.\", \"from\": 1511, \"to\": 1605, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Critics\", \"from\": 1511, \"to\": 1518}, {\"ngram\": \"their value\", \"from\": 1528, \"to\": 1539}, {\"ngram\": \"a world\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1551}, {\"ngram\": \"climate warming\", \"from\": 1567, \"to\": 1582}, {\"ngram\": \"other emergencies\", \"from\": 1587, \"to\": 1604}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Potential host cities became so Games-averse that Paris and Los Angeles were the only remaining candidates in 2017 when theInternational Olympic Committeeselected them for 2024 and 2028, respectively.\", \"from\": 1606, \"to\": 1806, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1656, \"end\": 1661, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3770163784666136e-30, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1666, \"end\": 1677, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.1022937469770596e-16, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Potential host cities\", \"from\": 1606, \"to\": 1627}, {\"ngram\": \"the only remaining candidates\", \"from\": 1683, \"to\": 1712}, {\"ngram\": \"theInternational Olympic\", \"from\": 1726, \"to\": 1750}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After scandals and the $13 billion cost of the pandemic-delayed Tokyo Games in 2021, unfulfilled promises of beneficial change for host Rio de Janeiro in 2016 and the 2014 Winter Games in Sochi tarnished by Russian doping and President Vladimir Putin's subsequent land grabs in Ukraine, the Switzerland-based IOC has mountains of skepticism to dispel.\", \"from\": 1808, \"to\": 2159, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1944, \"end\": 1958, \"title\": \"http